comments.body:
Steps to reproduce:

* Set up a Eucalyptus cloud in Managed Mode (1 x CLC/Walrus, 1 x CC/SC) with  AutoScaling and CloudWatch enabled.
* Create AS launch config:
{code}
euscale-create-launch-config JenkinsSwarmDemo --image-id emi-2A773CF3 --instance-type m1.medium -f cloud-init-jenkins-slave.config --key euca-admin
{code}
* Create AS group:
{code}
euscale-create-auto-scaling-group JenkinsScalingGroup --launch-configuration JenkinsSwarmDemo --availability-zones LayinDaSmackDown --min-size 2 --max-size 4 --default-cooldown 1 --grace-period 1
{code}
* Create AS policy:
{code}
euscale-put-scaling-policy JenkinsScalePolicy --auto-scaling-group JenkinsScalingGroup --adjustment=1 --type ChangeInCapacity --cooldown 1
{code}
* Add Cloudwatch Alarm Metric:
{code}
euwatch-put-metric-alarm AddJenkinsCapacity --comparison-operator LessThanThreshold --metric-name "Free Executors" --namespace "Jenkins" --period 60 --evaluation-periods 5 --statistic Minimum --threshold 1 --alarm-actions arn:aws:autoscaling::441445882805:scalingPolicy:00830b7d-33ed-4f4f-9459-e38f5b6f5126:autoScalingGroupName/JenkinsScalingGroup:policyName/JenkinsScalePolicy
{code}
* Start up monitoring script that populates metric data for CloudWatch.  The monitoring script I used can be found here - https://gist.github.com/viglesiasce/6012546
* After the alarm state has reached _OK_, trigger the alarm manually:
{code}
euwatch-set-alarm-state AddJenkinsCapacity --state-value ALARM --state-reason "Jenkins Demo"
{code}
* After the AS group has been fully populated (i.e. max-size has been met), check instance public/private IPs via euca-describe-isntances.  If the error hasn't showed up, terminate all the AS instances:
{code}
euscale-update-auto-scaling-group JenkinsScalingGroup --launch-configuration JenkinsSwarmDemo --availability-zones LayinDaSmackDown --min-size 0 --max-size 0 --desired-capacity 0
{code}
* After instances have been terminated, reset autoscaling group to original settings, and trigger alarm again.  This error first started showing up after running this cycle about 10 times.  Once I hit it, the issue would show up from there on out.  

Hope this helps.  Let me know if you have any additional questions.
